==Latin==

===Etymology===
'''abbas''' - From Greek [[αββας]], from Hebrew [[אב|אָב]] (av = 'father').

'''Abbas''' - From Arabic عباس ('abbaas): one who frowns a lot. عبس ('Abasa) = 'He Frowned': title of the 80th [[sura]] of the [[Qur'an]].

===Noun===
'''abbās (abbāt-)''' ''m'' ''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third declension|3rd declension]]'' (''Feminine:'' [[abbatissa]])

#an [[abbot]]
#a male [[given name]]

